      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://www.usepylon.com"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tired of juggling support conversations across Slack DMs, cluttered email inboxes, and Microsoft Teams chats? For growing B2B companies, managing fragmented customer communications is a surefire way to let critical issues slip through the cracks. That’s where ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " comes in—a dedicated B2B support platform built to consolidate your channels and supercharge your team with intelligent automation. In this step-by-step Pylon tutorial, I’ll walk you through exactly how to set it up and use it to bring order to the chaos.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Why You Need a Platform Like Pylon for B2B Support",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Let’s be real: your standard helpdesk or CRM might be great for e-commerce or B2C, but it often falls short for complex B2B relationships. B2B support involves longer sales cycles, multiple stakeholders, and deep product integration. Conversations happen in the tools your clients already use—like Slack and Teams. Trying to force these into a traditional ticketing system creates friction and dead ends.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-pylon"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon was designed from the ground up for this reality. Instead of moving conversations *out* of Slack, it brings powerful support workflows *into* them. It treats each channel—Slack, email, Teams—as a first-class citizen, giving you a unified view without disrupting your customers’ flow. This isn’t just another helpdesk; it’s a strategic upgrade for your entire customer-facing operation. If you’re evaluating options, understanding ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "why to choose Pylon",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " is key.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 1: Connecting Your Channels & Initial Setup",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Getting started with Pylon is refreshingly straightforward. The first step is connecting the communication channels where your clients already reach out.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://www.usepylon.com"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1.  ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Sign Up & Onboarding:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Head to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon’s website",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and schedule a demo. Their team specializes in B2B, so they’ll understand your setup immediately. During onboarding, they’ll help you map out your support structure.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2.  ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Connect Slack:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " This is Pylon’s standout integration. You’ll authorize Pylon to access specific Slack channels or DMs. I recommend creating dedicated support channels (e.g., #client-support-acme-corp) for major accounts. Pylon will automatically start creating tickets from messages in these channels.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3.  ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Connect Email:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Link your team’s shared support email (like support@yourcompany.com). Pylon’s AI engine instantly parses incoming emails, pulling them into your unified queue.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4.  ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Connect Microsoft Teams:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Similar to Slack, you connect relevant Teams channels. This is a game-changer for clients who operate primarily in the Microsoft ecosystem.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Within an hour, you’ll have a central “inbox” that aggregates every customer conversation, regardless of where it started. No more copy-pasting or manually logging tickets.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 2: Mastering the Unified Support Inbox",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Once connected, the Pylon dashboard becomes your mission control. Here’s how to leverage it:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "View & Triage:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " All incoming tickets appear in a single stream. You can filter by channel (Slack, Email, Teams), priority, or assignee. The interface is clean and fast—no bloat.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Internal Collaboration:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " This is where Pylon shines for B2B. You can @mention teammates *within a ticket* to loop in experts, and they can respond directly from Pylon or their connected Slack. All internal notes stay private, while client-facing replies are published to the original channel.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "SLA Tracking:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Set up response and resolution time targets. Pylon’s dashboard gives you a clear, at-a-glance view of which tickets are at risk of breaching SLAs, so you can proactively manage workload.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The real magic is in the seamless context. A ticket originating from a Slack thread keeps that entire conversation history attached, so any team member can jump in fully informed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 3: Leveraging AI-Powered Automation",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon isn’t just a consolidation tool; it’s an intelligent one. The AI-native features are designed to eliminate repetitive work and surface insights.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Automated Tagging & Routing:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Pylon’s AI analyzes ticket content and can automatically apply tags (e.g., “Billing,” “API Issue,” “Onboarding”) and even route tickets to the appropriate team or individual based on predefined rules.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Suggested Replies:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " For common questions, the AI can suggest replies from your knowledge base or past ticket resolutions. Your agents can accept, tweak, and send them in seconds, ensuring consistency and speed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Customer Sentiment Analysis:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " The platform can flag tickets that indicate frustration or high urgency, helping your team prioritize emotional escalations before they blow up.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/pylon-new-features"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "To unlock the full potential, explore the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "latest new features Pylon releases",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", as they consistently add powerful AI-driven capabilities tailored for B2B use cases.",
            "marks": []
          }
