          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "THEN",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " send a proactive message to the relevant client’s Slack channel: “Hi team, we’ve identified an issue affecting X. Our engineers are on it and we’ll update you in 15 minutes.”",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4.  ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "THEN",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " create a public status page incident.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/pylon-use-cases"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This kind of proactive, automated communication builds immense trust with B2B clients. You can also create macros—single-click templates that combine a public reply with internal actions, like updating a ticket’s status and sending a notification. For inspiration, ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
