    "image_prompt": "Editorial tech thumbnail, 16:9. Incorporate the brand logo fetched from https://logo.clearbit.com/usepylon.com as the clean focal element over a soft amber-to-cream gradient (Notion + Apple aesthetic). A clean, modern dashboard view showing unified tickets from Slack and email, with a subtle AI icon indicating automation.. Glassmorphism cards, soft volumetric light, generous negative space for a title, no embedded text, no watermark. --ar 16:9 --style raw",
    "faq_items": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can Pylon replace our Slack or Teams app entirely?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "No, and that’s by design. Pylon enhances your existing Slack and Teams experience by adding powerful support ticketing and automation directly within them. Your team and clients continue using their preferred apps, while Pylon works in the background to manage and organize conversations.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does Pylon's AI handle data privacy and security?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon is built with enterprise-grade security. It is SOC 2 Type II compliant, encrypts data in transit and at rest, and offers features like SSO and role-based access control. The AI processes data to provide suggestions and automation but does not store or learn from your confidential customer data beyond what’s necessary for the service.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Is there a free trial or a low-commitment way to start?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pylon offers a guided demo and setup process rather than a standard self-serve free trial, due to its focus on personalized B2B implementation. Their Starter plan begins at $59 per seat/month (billed annually) with a 3-seat minimum, making it a cost-effective entry point for teams serious about professionalizing their support stack.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
